# Sync Keybindings After Edits

## Mandatory Pre-Done Gate

Before reporting "done" or completing any task, the agent MUST:
1. Check: did this session modify `~/Library/Application Support/Cursor/User/keybindings.json`?
   - This includes direct edits, auto-promotion of Layer 2 commands, or adding new keybindings via the cursor-command-proxy skill.
2. If YES and keybinding sync has not been run yet in this session: STOP. Run the sync step below first.
3. If NO: proceed normally.

## Sync Step

Run:
```bash
bash ~/.cursor/scripts/sync_keybindings.sh sync
```

This will:
1. Export live keybindings to `~/.cursor/keybindings/keybindings.json` (canonical copy)
2. Commit and push to git
3. SSH to macOS targets only (`huh.laptop.us`) to pull and import
4. Linux hosts are skipped entirely (no SSH, no git pull)

## Scope

- This rule only covers keybinding sync
- It does NOT trigger the full toolbox sync (SyncOrchestrator / ChangeReviewer)
- Linux hosts catch up on keybinding git commits during their next regular toolbox sync
